    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-06-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-06-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="360"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d360">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 341.622a/150</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-06-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 9, 1916, noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received June 10, 4.50 p.
                        m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3978. <persName corresp="#p_JGEGV1">Von Jagow</persName> again asked me why notes
                    sent to Great Britain about the <hi rend="italic">China</hi> and post [mail]
                    were not published, as it would make good impression here. He said that he hoped
                    President and you would not be affected by what was said in the Reichstag
                    against the peace mediation of the President.<note n="1" xml:id="d360fn1">See
                        the Ambassador’s telegram No. 3941, May 31, 1916, <hi rend="italic"
                            >ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_33">p. 33</ref>.</note> He said that I knew
                    the position of Government here.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GJW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gerard</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
